trend_summary: 2000-s to 2020-s imagery shows steady infill around the central campus and commercial corridors, replacing vacant lots with low-mid-rise blocks while road layouts stay constant. Eastern grid intensifies, but western forest, river bends and golf course remain largely intact, preserving green buffers. Net effect is moderate densification without major sprawl.
notable_changes: Central institutional precinct gains several new academic/administrative buildings and parking decks.
Residential infill east of the main avenue converts open plots to continuous housing rows.
Retail/warehouse strips along the northeast arterial expand roof area and impervious cover.
Stadium complex in the southeast receives upgraded stands and resurfaced sports fields.
Western forest and riverfront show negligible encroachment, highlighting conservation stability.
